  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is currently a trans-Tasman collaborative research project underway between the Australian Centre for International Agricultural Research, New Zealand&apos;s Ministry for Primary Industries, and Australia&apos;s national research agency (CSIRO) to develop innovative decision making tools that can map transformational options at a regional level to&#xA0;allow exploration and planning for future food systems. MFAT has been asked to contribute funding&#xA0; for a case study in Samoa for the research.</narrative>
